.TH "gsm_error" 9 "gsm_error" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gsm_error \- handle tty error
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" gsm_error
.BI "(struct gsm_mux *gsm "  ","
.BI "unsigned char data "  ","
.BI "unsigned char flag "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gsm" 12
ldisc data
.IP "data" 12
byte received (may be invalid)
.IP "flag" 12
error received

Handle an error in the receipt of data for a frame. Currently we just
go back to hunting for a SOF.

